{"claim_id": "claim_001", "text": "In mass spectrometry imaging, adducts can form between target molecules such as metabolites and other substances such as matrix or salt ions.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "In mass spectrometry imaging, adducts can form between target molecules (e.g. metabolites) and other substances such as matrix or salt ions.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [0, 144], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_ADDUCTS_DATASET"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_007", "text": "An adduct refers specifically to a transformation caused by the addition of a chemical moiety, often during the MSI procedure.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "An *adduct* refers specifically to a transformation caused by the addition of a chemical moiety, often during the MSI procedure.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [1792, 1919], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_008", "text": "The precursor to an adduct is called the parent ion or parent molecule.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "The precursor to an adduct is the *parent* ion/molecule.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [1986, 2034], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_009", "text": "The mass2adduct analysis looks at pairs of peaks and attempts to match their massdiffs to known chemical transformations to find adducts derived from the chemical matrix used for MALDI-MSI.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "In our analysis we look at pairs of peaks (*peak pairs*, *ion pairs*), and attempt to match their massdiffs to known chemical transformations, in order to find adducts derived from the chemical matrix used for MALDI-MSI.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [2035, 2226], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["SYS_MASS2ADDUCT", "COMP_ADDUCTS_DATASET", "ARCH_WORKFLOW"]}
