{"claim_id": "claim_032", "text": "adductMatch can be applied to a massdiff object to add a matches column listing the closest-matching adduct for each ion pair.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "We can match massdiffs to specific adduct types using the same function `adductMatch` that we applied to the histogram above. This adds an additional column to the `massdiff` object called `matches`, which lists the closest-matching adduct (if any) corresponding to a given ion pair.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [5984, 6257], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_MASSDIFF_OBJ", "TOOL_MASSDIFF_FN", "TOOL_ADDUCTMATCH", "CONCEPT_MASSDIFF"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_033", "text": "The object produced by adductMatch is a subset of the original massdiff object, as ion pairs without a matching adduct are excluded.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "The object `d.diff.annot` is a subset of the original `d.diff` object, as ion pairs without a matching adduct are excluded.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [6373, 6498], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_MASSDIFF_OBJ", "TOOL_MASSDIFF_FN", "TOOL_ADDUCTMATCH", "CONCEPT_MASSDIFF"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_034", "text": "corrPairsMSI performs a correlation test on each pair of peaks in a massdiff object.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "This performs a correlation test (by default two-tailed with Pearson's method) on each pair of peaks in the massdiff object.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [6650, 6788], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_MASSDIFF_OBJ", "TOOL_MASSDIFF_FN", "TOOL_CORRPAIRSMSI", "CONCEPT_MASSDIFF"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_035", "text": "corrPairsMSI uses the two-tailed Pearson method by default for correlation testing.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "This performs a correlation test (by default two-tailed with Pearson's method) on each pair of peaks in the massdiff object.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [6650, 6788], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_MASSDIFF_OBJ", "TOOL_MASSDIFF_FN", "TOOL_CORRPAIRSMSI", "CONCEPT_MASSDIFF"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_041", "text": "Correlation test results in corrPairsMSI output include Estimate (correlation coefficient), P.value, and Significance.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "The correlation tests results will be added to the massdiff object, with three values reported: `Estimate` (correlation coefficient), `P.value`, and `Significance` (whether or not p-value is below the threshold after Bonferroni correction).", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_mass2adduct/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [7478, 7729], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": "10.1021/acs.analchem.0c04720", "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_MASSDIFF_OBJ", "TOOL_MASSDIFF_FN", "TOOL_CORRPAIRSMSI", "CONCEPT_MASSDIFF"]}
